summary: This document is an email chain regarding a late travel voucher submission for a DOJ trip to Santa Monica from September 17-20, 2019. The trip's purpose was witness interviews for the case 'U.S. v. Epstein' (R19NYS13842). The correspondence shows administrative follow-up on reimbursement.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip to Santa Monica
events.description: A DOJ trip to Santa Monica for witness interviews related to U.S. v. Epstein case R19NYS13842.

keyFacts: A DOJ travel voucher was issued for a trip to Santa Monica from September 17-20, 2019, for witness interviews in the U.S. v. Epstein case (R19NYS13842).
The email chain from October 3, 2019, shows administrative follow-up regarding the late submission of the travel voucher for reimbursement.
The document references EOUSA (Executive Office for United States Attorneys) in the context of addressing automated email issues.
The traveler's name is redacted in the document.
